Name: Olan
Description: Location We currently have two restaurant in Providencia: -Av. Condell # 200, Providencia. Not to be confused with the street Condell that comes after Rancagua If you travel by car from the East, go down Providencia, after Salvador there is access to Condell on the left. Once on Condell, the reference is Quebec with Condell. If you travel by car from the centre, go up the Alameda that becomes Providencia. You need to turn right into Condell. Once on Condell, the reference is Quebec with Condell. -Av. Seminario #67, providencia. If travelling by car from the West, take the street Francisco Bilbao and turn right into the street Seminario. If travelling by car from the center, take the street Diagonal Paraguay that turns into Rancagua. Cross ParqueBustamente and then turn left.

Name: Puerto Bellavista
Description: Puerto Bellavista, especializado en pescados y mariscos con preparaciones chilenas, rememora los puertos de Chile que se ven plasmados en su decoracion, ambiente, y por supuesto en cada uno de sus platos. En su carta encontraras platos como �Merluza a la lata con mariscos y verduras� que es parte de nuestra Tradicion de Caleta, �Ostiones y Pinzas de Jaiba, sobre papas nativas con mote y cebollin� de las Aventuras del Capitan, o un �Jardin de Mariscos� de nuestras Joyas del Puerto. Los invitamos a adentrarse en el puerto y vivir la esencia del mar que nos rodea de norte a sur, con la picardia y sensualidad del marisco, y el esfuerzo y tenacidad del pescador; platos con tradicion que te despertaran tus sentidos y te llevaran al hogar de los amantes del mar.
Directions: Pio Nono 77 | Patio Bellavista, Constitucin 30-70, Providencia, Santiago 7530280, Chile

Name: Le Petit Bernard
Description: Traditional French food with specialty in fish of the day. With only 22 seats, the menu is short because you want to offer the maximum freshness of the products, with preparations of the day. The fixed menu includes the traditional ones like boeuf borgignon, rabbit or onion soup, and fish and seafood are always special of the day because they depend on the daily availability of the products. Our chef Bernard buys daily at dawn the fish and seafood that will use, which allow to guarantee freshness. The wine list is also brief but original. We work only with natural wines, similar to an organic wine (although in reality that concept does not exist for wines). The natural wines do not have addition of sulphites and that makes them very special, although the offer is reduced, it is worth.

Name: The Black Rock Pub
Description: We are a cosy pub that sells great tasting Chilean micro-brewery beers and we serve tasty food that goes well with the beers. We offer traditional Fish'n Chips, Hamburgers or you can try the Chilean Chorrillana. These meals and snacks, + others, are only served after 19:00, Monday to Friday, all day Saturdays Between 12:30 - 15:30 we offer a menu of the day for the Chilean office workers. We have outdoor seating, great in summer, and inside is a smoke free area. We show many international sports: AFL, NRL, Cricket, Rugby Union, NHL, NFL, MLB, Premier League. Directions: Avda. Providencia 2528.We are down one block from Tobalaba Metro and close to the corner of Holanda and Providencia. We are not easy to find when you are standing on the main street but if you look for a tall palm tree next to a shop called  Farmacias del Dr. Simi then you will see an entrance to a small galleria. Walk down into the galleria entrance and you will see a terrace with table and chairs. These tables and chairs belong to us. We are directly to the right of the entrance and down a set of steps. We hope to see you sometime soon.

Description: CAFETERIA AND SPECIALTY TETERYWe work with our own coffee, thanks to that, we can offer a freshly roasted coffee with the highest quality standards. You can even enjoy our families with different types of products and services at the perfect temperature.KITCHENWe offer a lacto-vegetarian menu with vegan and omniborous options. Pizzas, Salads, Sandwich, Presses, Salmon Carpaccio, Provoletas, Quesadillas, Mushroom Ceviche and more!BELGIAN PASTRYAll the pastry corresponds to the interpretation of European and Belgian recipes made with imported raw material. Cakes, Cinnamon Roll, Belgian Volcano, Muffins, Waffles and much more enjoy enjoying all the time!FREE PRODUCTSNow everyone can enjoy the rich and healthy food without Gluten and TACC,Free of Milk, casein, lactose, soy, egg, nuts, peanuts and dyes in Cupcakes, Brownies, Biscuits and Flaxseed Bread with what prepares the exquisite Montaditos!You can also enjoy Fresh Almond Milk with which you can prepare in the cafeteria and you can buy it to go! Check for availability or monthly registrations.BOUTIQUE AND WAREHOUSEStvico Boutique offers a wide range of mostly handmade products. Women, Men, Kids and Baby, Jewelry, Stationery and Decoration, some of the things they can find.In Warehouse we have gourmet products to take like Cucumbers By Maria, Amma Ghee and much more!FACILITIESEnjoy with all your family in Stvico.We have an entertaining children sector thought for them where to eat and read books. Get in touch with your children in the baths (man and woman) and send them to the table in beautiful wooden chairs!If you come with your pet, we have a sector and a menu thought for them.CONCERT COFFEEWhat better way to end the week having a good time, we hope you enjoy Sunday the best selection of live music for you. Ideal to come with the whole family, friends, couple, etc.BICYCLE PARKINGIf you come by bike, we have a special parking for you. The Taller Blanco provides us with its facilities so that you can be more at ease when it comes to parking your travel companion. Just come to any of us and we'll help you right away!

Description: Being Chile a long country with a wide coast to the Pacific Ocean, Maria del Mar has been treasured to have a diverse range of seafood. Name: Kukara Macara
Description: Phone: 809.241.3143This restaurant has the Old West theme. All the waiters are dressed like Cowboys. Prices are reasonable for foreigners. Location is great (right across from the Monument). I had a Pincho Mixto (shish-ka-bob/skewer of chicken and beef) with rice. My girlfriend had a chicken nugget like appetizer (wasnt a lot of chicken in there, but she doesnt eat much). Service was great. Add my two bottle cokes (ice cold) and a shot of Brugal Rum and a lemonade. Bill was $25 USD. I would definitely recommend this place to anyone after or before visiting the Monument.

Name: Ciudad Vieja
Description: In our Ciudad Vieja, you are welcome to the restaurant on the pictures corner of the neighborhood. And here you can rediscover the real pleasure of eating, the simple and fulfilling, delicious taste of good food. Entering our Ciudad Vieja means crossing the threshold of old time traditional kitchen, where the tasty smells whirl around magically and the flavours recall delightful experiences, where the hospitality makes you stay longer and always come back. And it is also the simplest and fresh ingredients, which modestly offer the luxurious pleasures of excellent food. Ciudad Vieja is our kitchen, our dining area, the place where we invite you to feel at home: to come in when you want, to eat what you want and however you want... And above all, to make this Sangucheria your place much as it is ours.
Cuisines: Bar, Chilean, Brew Pub, Vegetarian Friendly
